column2: Green algee plumes are prevelent on the north end of the lake. Pieces of these plumes washed up with the ice at ice out on the 30th of April.
An algae bloom over the weekend significantly reduced water clarity.
First algae die back occurred on the 6th of July.
The second algae bloom died back on 08/29/2016
Mats of common water wort began washing up on shore on 7/7 and continue.
Plant material continues to wash up on the north shore.
Plant material continues to wash up on the north shore.
After a storm on 7/28- no new plant material washed up on the north shore.
Fern Pond Weed began washing up on shore on the first of August. New algae bloom on 8/3
The fern pond weed continues to wash up and algae bloom continues.
New algae bloom after storm on 9/2
Algae present in the water column.
Ice out on 4/2/20- water was dark and murky- 1st water chem test canceled due to Covid-19.
The first algae bloom of the year started this morning but stopped and the water cleared up by noon.
First major algae bloom occurred on 7/2/20
Last water chemistry for the year.
This is the first time that the water in Big Doctor lacked any tannin staining in the 12 years that I have been doing this. So- for the first time I'm able to list the water color as blue.
